### Type Conversion Methods

Dart provides methods to convert between different data types.

### String to Number

```dart
void main() {
  // String to int
  int a = int.parse('42');

  // String to double
  double b = double.parse('3.14');

  // Using tryParse to avoid exceptions
  int? c = int.tryParse('not_a_number'); // Returns null

  print('$a, $b, $c');
}
```

### Number to String

```dart
void main() {
  int value = 42;
  String str1 = value.toString();
  String str2 = 3.14159.toStringAsFixed(2); // '3.14'

  print('$str1, $str2');
}
```

### Type Checking and Casting

```dart
void main() {
  dynamic value = 'Hello';

  // Type check with 'is'
  if (value is String) {
    print('Length: ${value.length}'); // value is promoted to String
  }

  // Explicit cast with 'as'
  String text = value as String;
  print(text);
}
```

| Method | From | To |
|--------|------|----|
| `int.parse()` | String | int |
| `double.parse()` | String | double |
| `.toString()` | Any | String |
| `.toStringAsFixed(n)` | double | String (fixed decimals) |
| `.toInt()` | double | int |
| `.toDouble()` | int | double |

> **Key Point:** Always use `tryParse()` instead of `parse()` when you are not certain the string is a valid number. It returns `null` instead of throwing an exception.

codeExample:
void main() {
  // String to number
  String ageStr = '25';
  int age = int.parse(ageStr);

  // Number to string
  double pi = 3.14159;
  String piStr = pi.toStringAsFixed(2);

  // Type check
  dynamic data = 'Hello, Dart!';
  if (data is String) {
    print('String length: ${data.length}');
  }

  print('Age: $age, Pi: $piStr');
}
